### setIpiTypes() {#aeed3cbd5a284d43852203231c865d301}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void llvm::codeview::TypeDumpVisitor::setIpiTypes (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/codeview/typecollection">TypeCollection</a> &amp; Types)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
When dumping types from an IPI stream in a PDB, a type index may refer to a type or an item <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/callingconv/#abdf8cf606905c10634e831390981b0ed">ID</a>.

The dumper will lookup the &quot;name&quot; of the index in the item database if appropriate. If ItemDB is null, it will use TypeDB, which is correct when dumping types from an object file (/Z7).

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/codeview/typedumpvisitor-h/#l00038">38</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/codeview/typedumpvisitor-h">TypeDumpVisitor.h</a>.

<MemberDefinition

Get the database of indices for the stream that we are dumping.

If ItemDB is set, then we must be dumping an item (IPI) stream. This will also always get the appropriate DB for printing item names.
